race.comment: CAPTAINS KNOCK (13) is in career best form and made it six wins in a row when too good for a handy field including tonight's rival SWAYZEE in a 2m victory at Menangle last time. Jumps in distance but came from this row to win The Bidgee at Wagga over a similar journey last month. Hard to tip against him in his current form. SWAYZEE (14) has 2.5m to make up on CAPTAINS KNOCK through their Menangle clash but that was his first outing for 10 weeks and he strikes at 50 per cent when second-up so is sure to be improved. Unbeaten both here and the distance including a win in this race last year. Big danger tonight. RIPP (8) drew wide and worked when midfield to CAPTAINS KNOCK last start. Racing consistently prior and has won four of six attempts here so looks likely to figure in the exotics along with I BREAK THE LINE (7) who has placed behind CAPTAINS KNOCK and another topliner in Don Hugo in his last two outings.
